      "text": [
        " الْأَرْضِ لِيُفْسِدَ فِيها وَ يُهْلِكَ الْحَرْثَ وَ النَّسْلَ بِظُلْمِهِ وَ سُوءِ سِيرَتِهِ وَ اللَّهُ لا يُحِبُّ الْفَسادَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473564\">H 14883</a> – A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Muhammad Bin Salmaan Al-Azdy, from Abu Al-Jaroud, from Abu Is’haq, who has narrated the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>mir-ul- Momineen</span><sup>asws</sup> said regarding <span class=\"ibTxt\">“<a href=\"/#/books/quran:2#h205\"><a href=\"/books/quran:2#h205\">[2:205]</a></a> And when he turns back, he runs along in the land that he may cause mischief in it and destroy the tilth and the stock”</span>, by his injustices, and his evil ways <span class=\"ibTxt\">“and Allah does not love mischief-making”</span>. "
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "436. Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Ibn Ra’ab, from Humraan Bin Ayn, who has narrated the following: Abu Ja’far (a.s.) said (referring to the ‘Tahreef in Quran) in this “<a href=\"/#/books/quran:2#h257\"><a href=\"/books/quran:2#h257\">[2:257]</a></a> and (as to) those who disbelieve, their guardians are the tyrants”. ‘الطَّوَاغِيتُ’ instead of ‘الطَّاغُوتُ’ (which is in Quran we have these days)."
        ]
      }
    },
